I can schedule node-cron to run every minute or every thirty seconds (see code), but I&#39;d like it to run half-past every minute. The reason why is I also have another task scheduled once per hour and I&#39;d like the minute task to be complete before the hourly task is run.

The minute task reads Modbus values and logs to a MongoDB database. The hourly task grabs all of the records and POSTs them to a REST endpoint and logs the sync time. Because both tasks run at the same time on the hour, one value is left out of the POST.


```JavaScript
